column5: One dead fry today but thats not bad Richard
Guess there must of been a first off of this somewhere on the forum.What are you hatching?

OK go up to my post and read the video heading, no just kidding, I've got a few post on putting a in Class Salmon Hatchery at our local school, it's a 20 gal Aquarium that had about 100 Eggs put in it & I'm trying to do weekly up dates on a few Forums & to the Lake Huron Fishing Club were I got the Eggs, some of the Guys & Gals seem interested so I'll try to keep everybody informed, we are hoping to expand this next year & have some people interested, there are other organization in the Province doing this, but I'm one of the few promoting it so openly hoping it'll grow Richard
No worries my fault. Are they chinock?  Looking forward to the progress.
Yes there Chinook, just back from changing some water & feeding Richard
